The paper proposes a new algorithm for non-negative matrix factorization and analyzes its theoretical properties, making it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The algorithm is based on gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the robustness of the algorithm to noise, which is a common concern in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents empirical results on synthetic datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of computational statistics (cs.SI).
